From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Catalin Rapiteanu <viorel-catalin.rapiteanu@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] gencontrol: Replace gcc-14-for-host with gcc-14 in headers
 dependency

The linux-rt-headers package has a runtime Depends on gcc-14-for-host,
which is a cross-compilation virtual package not available in the STX
repositories. Replace it with gcc-14 which is available and sufficient
for building out-of-tree kernel modules on the native architecture.

Signed-off-by: Catalin Rapiteanu <viorel-catalin.rapiteanu@windriver.com>
---
 debian/bin/gencontrol.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/debian/bin/gencontrol.py b/debian/bin/gencontrol.py
--- a/debian/bin/gencontrol.py
+++ b/debian/bin/gencontrol.py
@@ -419,7 +419,7 @@
                     desc.append(config.description.long[part])
                     desc.append_short(config.description.short[part])
 
-        packages_headers[0].depends.merge([relation_c_compiler_host])
+        packages_headers[0].depends.merge([relation_c_compiler])
         packages_own.extend(packages_image)
         packages_own.extend(packages_headers)
 
-- 
2.47.3
